WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:04.460
Dude, we have a test.
You have to focus.

00:04.460 --> 00:06.250
I have no motivation
to succeed.

00:06.250 --> 00:08.170
You don't understand
how hard it is to study

00:08.170 --> 00:09.830
when you know you're sitting on
a huge trust fund.

00:09.830 --> 00:12.210
Dude, I'm so sorry, man --
I didn't realize.

00:13.790 --> 00:15.000
What do you guys think?

00:15.000 --> 00:16.790
"Charge"!
Scary, huh?

00:16.790 --> 00:18.670
Scary that some of this
might be passed down to me.

00:18.670 --> 00:21.330
War reenacting is a celebration
of our nation's history,

00:21.330 --> 00:22.080
and despite
what your mother says,

00:22.080 --> 00:23.330
that cannot be learned

00:23.330 --> 00:24.380
by watching
Kevin Costner movies.

00:24.380 --> 00:26.540
I don't get why you care so much
about history.

00:26.540 --> 00:28.420
It's just a bunch
of boring facts and dates.

00:28.420 --> 00:29.880
Boring facts --

00:29.880 --> 00:31.500
Why are you being so mean?!

00:31.500 --> 00:33.540
History is the story
of living, breathing people

00:33.540 --> 00:34.670
who helped
shape our world.

00:34.670 --> 00:35.790
Oh, yeah?

00:35.790 --> 00:37.040
If they're so great,

00:37.040 --> 00:40.210
then why are they dead?

00:40.210 --> 00:43.830
Guess who is killing it
as the Spring Gala Chairperson.

00:43.830 --> 00:47.750
[ As '80s rocker ] ♪ Is it
my laaaady, Kaaaaatie? ♪

00:47.750 --> 00:49.040
What are you doing?

00:49.040 --> 00:50.170
I'm not sure.

00:50.170 --> 00:52.000
I'm starting to rack up
awesome stuff

00:52.000 --> 00:52.960
for the charity auction --

00:52.960 --> 00:54.670
a $100 gas card,

00:54.670 --> 00:56.420
10 free games
of mini-golf,

00:56.420 --> 00:58.580
and a signed head shot
of Scott Bakula

00:58.580 --> 00:59.710
that I stole
from the dry cleaner.

00:59.710 --> 01:01.710
Cooper: [ Laughing ]

01:01.710 --> 01:03.750
Oh, I'm laughing 'cause you said
those things are awesome,

01:03.750 --> 01:05.960
and they so aren't. Katie:
I'm beginning to understand

01:05.960 --> 01:08.000
why your parents travel
so much.

01:08.000 --> 01:09.670
Mom, Cooper's right.

01:09.670 --> 01:11.290
Gas cards
aren't gonna cut it.

01:11.290 --> 01:14.380
To raise big money, you need
big-ticket auction items.

01:14.380 --> 01:16.380
Last year,
Nancy Granville's family donated

01:16.380 --> 01:18.080
a week
at her Sun Valley house.

01:18.080 --> 01:19.920
Brought in $20,000.

01:19.920 --> 01:21.380
That's like 10 allowances.

01:25.080 --> 01:26.080
Cooper,
you spilled your milk.

01:26.080 --> 01:27.250
Sorry about that.

01:27.250 --> 01:28.830
Are you going
to just leave it?

01:28.830 --> 01:30.170
Well,
what else would I do?

01:30.170 --> 01:32.830
What happens at your house
when you spill something?

01:35.880 --> 01:37.170
And now what happens?

01:37.170 --> 01:39.380
Well, Lupe or Dolores
or Lita or Patricia

01:39.380 --> 01:40.710
will come in
and clean it up.

01:40.710 --> 01:42.790
It is...Tuesday,

01:42.790 --> 01:46.290
so it would be Lupe, Dolores,
Lita, Patricia, or the driver.

01:46.290 --> 01:47.620
I don't know his name.

01:47.620 --> 01:49.000
We just call him Bentley
because, you know --

01:49.000 --> 01:50.750
Shut this up!
Clean this up!

01:50.750 --> 01:52.170
See?
This kind of behavior

01:52.170 --> 01:54.330
is exactly why I don't want to
be a part of Westport culture.

01:54.330 --> 01:56.210
These people
have no sense of reality.

01:56.210 --> 01:57.380
Oliver: Mom, if you don't
raise enough cash,

01:57.380 --> 01:59.420
it'll bring shame
to our family.

01:59.420 --> 02:01.210
It'll be Dad's goatee
all over again.

02:01.210 --> 02:03.080
Oliver, you have to accept
that your mother and I

02:03.080 --> 02:05.710
don't subscribe to
the shallow values of this town.

02:05.710 --> 02:07.210
As for the goatee...

02:07.210 --> 02:08.880
"Reality Bites" pushed
a lot of good people

02:08.880 --> 02:10.290
in a lot
of bad directions.

02:10.290 --> 02:12.830
Okay, shame doesn't work
with you people.

02:12.830 --> 02:14.330
Let's try facts.

02:14.330 --> 02:15.830
If you don't raise
enough money,

02:15.830 --> 02:17.750
it'll force the school
to cut back on things

02:17.750 --> 02:19.250
like the Special Ed
department.

02:20.460 --> 02:22.460
Hmm.
That wouldn't be good.

02:22.460 --> 02:24.460
But on the bright side,
she is getting better.

02:24.460 --> 02:25.880
Yesterday she was scrubbing up
to her shoulders.

02:27.830 --> 02:29.420
Hup, there she goes.

02:29.420 --> 02:31.790
Fine. I'll sweet talk
the rich idiots.

02:31.790 --> 02:33.620
But for the record,
I hate it.

02:33.620 --> 02:34.960
Agreed.
People should donate

02:34.960 --> 02:36.040
because it's
the right thing to do,

02:36.040 --> 02:37.580
not because they get
some vacation in return.

02:37.580 --> 02:39.710
This is the kind of nonsense
I was telling you about.

02:39.710 --> 02:40.710
♪♪

02:44.380 --> 02:46.710
♪♪

02:46.710 --> 02:48.460
Taylor, I just talked
to your history teacher.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.380
In an effort to foster
your love for history,

02:50.380 --> 02:52.330
I'm taking you out of class and
bringing you to the reenactment.

02:52.330 --> 02:54.750
What if I didn't go
to the reenactment,

02:54.750 --> 02:56.750
and you just took me out
and dropped me off at the mall?

02:56.750 --> 02:58.290
No reenactment, no dice.

02:58.290 --> 02:59.380
You're lucky
I hate school.

02:59.380 --> 03:01.420
Question --
In this battle,

03:01.420 --> 03:03.420
how many died
and how bloody was it?

03:03.420 --> 03:05.290
Well, it was a massacre,
so almost everyone

03:05.290 --> 03:06.670
and very bloody.

03:06.670 --> 03:08.040
I want in.

03:08.040 --> 03:09.210
Come on!

03:09.210 --> 03:15.420
♪♪

03:15.420 --> 03:16.580
Nancy!

03:16.580 --> 03:18.620
Hi. Katie Otto.

03:18.620 --> 03:20.540
I'm chair of the Spring Gala
this year.

03:20.540 --> 03:22.880
Ohh.
Well, I hope you fair better

03:22.880 --> 03:25.210
than last year's chairperson,
Stacy Clouser.

03:25.210 --> 03:27.920
Do you know the pressure
of planning that Gala

03:27.920 --> 03:30.080
caused her to have
a nervous breakdown?

03:30.080 --> 03:31.380
I want to thank you

03:31.380 --> 03:32.960
for attending
this very important

03:32.960 --> 03:34.960
Spring Gala strategy meeting.

03:34.960 --> 03:36.380
After some brief remarks,

03:36.380 --> 03:38.380
I will open the room
to questions.

03:38.380 --> 03:42.420
Bup! After my remarks,
Mr. Bobbins.

03:42.420 --> 03:44.920
I'm pretty sure
that has all been exaggerated.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.330
Are you?
'Cause I was there

03:46.330 --> 03:47.960
when the paramedics
had to hold her down

03:47.960 --> 03:49.040
and administer
a sedative.

03:49.040 --> 03:50.330
But you know what,

03:50.330 --> 03:52.420
you tell yourself
whatever you need to hear.

03:52.420 --> 03:54.040
I'm just gonna come out with it.
Mm.

03:54.040 --> 03:57.420
Would you be willing to donate
your Sun Valley ski house

03:57.420 --> 03:58.580
to this year's
Gala auction?

04:02.710 --> 04:03.920
Oh, is that
your whole pitch?

04:03.920 --> 04:06.420
Um...

04:06.420 --> 04:08.620
How about I throw in
an almost-full punch card

04:08.620 --> 04:11.040
to Gary's Beef Bowl?
[ Scoffs ]

04:11.040 --> 04:12.540
No.

04:12.540 --> 04:13.920
[ Sighs ]

04:13.920 --> 04:15.880
It's just that
you donated it last year,

04:15.880 --> 04:17.420
and I thought maybe
you would do it again.

04:17.420 --> 04:19.290
And I thought that
my ex-husband liked women,

04:19.290 --> 04:21.080
so I guess we're both
cruelly disappointed.

04:24.460 --> 04:27.040
The thing is, we need
to get enough money

04:27.040 --> 04:29.920
to pay for things
like the Special Ed department.

04:30.880 --> 04:32.000
Hi! [ Chuckles ]

04:32.000 --> 04:33.290
Still here!

04:33.290 --> 04:34.750
Can't get rid of me
that easy!

04:34.750 --> 04:36.420
[ Laughs ]

04:40.040 --> 04:41.120
[ Groans ]

04:41.120 --> 04:46.670
♪♪

04:46.670 --> 04:48.710
You girls are in for a treat.
Over the next two days,

04:48.710 --> 04:50.210
we're gonna relive
the Westport Massacre --

04:50.210 --> 04:52.040
an event where real people
were inspired

04:52.040 --> 04:53.330
to stand up
against tyranny

04:53.330 --> 04:55.290
and change the course
of the nation.

04:55.290 --> 04:57.040
But they all got massacred,
right?

04:57.040 --> 04:58.250
Sure,
if you want to nitpick.

04:58.250 --> 05:01.080
Okay, here's where
the excitement begins.

05:01.080 --> 05:03.500
You get to choose
whatever you want to be --

05:03.500 --> 05:05.540
a soldier, a scout,
a musket loader --

05:05.540 --> 05:08.290
Actually, Corporal Otto, women
can't be whatever they want.

05:08.290 --> 05:10.210
They can only be
what's on this list.

05:13.330 --> 05:14.500
Not much of a list.

05:14.500 --> 05:16.710
Do I detect a tone
of insubordination?

05:16.710 --> 05:18.830
Sir, no, sir.
Corporal, we all understand

05:18.830 --> 05:20.920
the importance
of historical accuracy.

05:20.920 --> 05:22.460
Without that, we're just
a bunch of dorks

05:22.460 --> 05:24.290
running around a field.
And I'm not missing

05:24.290 --> 05:26.170
my once-a-month
supervised visitation day

05:26.170 --> 05:27.380
with my kid for that.

05:27.380 --> 05:29.120
[ Chuckles ]
In the real battle,

05:29.120 --> 05:31.620
the only females involved
were nurses.

05:31.620 --> 05:32.750
Is that understood?

05:32.750 --> 05:34.880
Yes, sir. Understood, sir. Good.

05:34.880 --> 05:36.540
Okay. Change of plans,

05:36.540 --> 05:38.290
but...also exciting.

05:38.290 --> 05:39.880
Think of how cool
being a nurse will be.

05:39.880 --> 05:41.330
You get to run
around the battlefield,

05:41.330 --> 05:42.920
carrying the wounded --
Correction.

05:42.920 --> 05:44.790
Nurses are confined
to the medical tent --

05:44.790 --> 05:47.080
nursing "wounds,"
tending to the "dead,"

05:47.080 --> 05:49.830
and preparing the hot stew which
was generously provided to us

05:49.830 --> 05:51.460
today by Chunky.

05:51.460 --> 05:53.040
[ Scoffs ]
History sucks.

05:53.040 --> 05:55.170
Yep, history sucks
for women.

05:55.170 --> 05:56.540
For men,
it was pretty all right.

05:56.540 --> 05:58.210
[ Chuckles ]

05:58.210 --> 06:03.380
♪♪

06:03.380 --> 06:06.210
There is a new name
on my hate list.

06:06.210 --> 06:07.670
Nancy Granville.

06:07.670 --> 06:08.750
How did you know?

06:08.750 --> 06:10.080
Oliver called us.

06:10.080 --> 06:11.750
He told us you struck out
with a bunch of moms

06:11.750 --> 06:12.710
at drop-off today.

06:12.710 --> 06:13.920
Oliver called you?

06:13.920 --> 06:15.620
Yep.
On the phone?

06:15.620 --> 06:17.080
To complain about me?

06:17.080 --> 06:19.540
He's worried
your Florida-ness --

06:19.540 --> 06:20.920
his words --

06:20.920 --> 06:22.790
is impeding your ability
to perform

06:22.790 --> 06:24.380
in the capacity
of Gala Chairperson.

06:24.380 --> 06:26.120
And as much as I hate
to admit it,

06:26.120 --> 06:28.120
that horrible child
is right.

06:28.120 --> 06:30.210
In Westport,
any charity donation

06:30.210 --> 06:32.250
comes from a quid pro quo.

06:32.250 --> 06:34.710
You want big items, you have
to give something in return.

06:34.710 --> 06:37.210
You know why Nancy Granville
donated her place in Sun Valley

06:37.210 --> 06:38.880
to the Gala last year?

06:38.880 --> 06:40.920
You don't know why!

06:40.920 --> 06:43.920
It's because Stacy Clouser gave
her use of her personal chef.

06:43.920 --> 06:45.830
For a week.
Hold on.

06:45.830 --> 06:48.420
So to get the people in Westport
to donate big, fancy items

06:48.420 --> 06:50.210
to the Gala, they need
a favor in return?

06:51.710 --> 06:54.170
But I don't have
anything of value to offer.

06:54.170 --> 06:56.080
You could let people
hunt Greg in the woods,

06:56.080 --> 06:57.540
"Most Dangerous Game" style.

06:57.540 --> 06:59.210
I'd pay good money for that.
Mnh-mnh.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.620
No one is hunting Greg.

07:00.620 --> 07:01.460
He's not spry.

07:01.460 --> 07:03.540
Fine.

07:03.540 --> 07:06.380
Well, I do have a $20,000
gold-embroidered sofa.

07:06.380 --> 07:08.080
You could offer it to Nancy
for her ski house.

07:08.080 --> 07:08.920
It's gorgeous.

07:08.920 --> 07:10.250
Why don't you keep it?

07:10.250 --> 07:12.250
It's too high.
It's humiliating.

07:12.250 --> 07:14.000
My legs dangle
like a ventriloquist dummy.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.670
I don't need your sofa

07:15.670 --> 07:18.460
because I refuse to buy
into this stupid Westport,

07:18.460 --> 07:19.540
rich-person,
horse-trading nonsense.

07:19.540 --> 07:20.750
Mm. Ah.

07:20.750 --> 07:23.710
Oh, Katie, hi.

07:23.710 --> 07:25.670
Hate to interrupt
your second feeding,

07:25.670 --> 07:27.040
but I heard
you're failing miserably

07:27.040 --> 07:28.460
at getting donations
for the Gala.

07:28.460 --> 07:32.880
Well, a $100 gas card
says otherwise.

07:32.880 --> 07:34.920
Actually $50.
I had to fill up.

07:34.920 --> 07:36.830
I want you to know that
I can't wait to laugh at you

07:36.830 --> 07:38.250
when this falls apart.

07:38.250 --> 07:39.880
Then I'll pretend
that I took it too far.

07:39.880 --> 07:41.080
Then I'll comfort you
just enough

07:41.080 --> 07:42.290
so that you think
it's real,

07:42.290 --> 07:43.790
and then I'll laugh some more
in your face.

07:43.790 --> 07:45.040
[ Chuckles ]

07:48.170 --> 07:50.170
Well, I'm not gonna fail.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.540
Because I just decided
to play the game.

07:52.540 --> 07:55.330
Big-ticket donations,
here I come.

07:55.330 --> 07:58.080
Great! I will give you $10,000
to hunt Greg!

07:58.080 --> 07:59.460
No one is hunting Greg!

07:59.460 --> 08:01.920
♪♪

08:05.000 --> 08:06.790
♪♪

08:06.790 --> 08:08.120
Nancy!
[ Groans ]

08:08.120 --> 08:09.880
How funny
to bump into you.

08:09.880 --> 08:11.580
Is it?
What do you want, Katie?

08:11.580 --> 08:13.250
I have a little something
I'd like to offer

08:13.250 --> 08:15.710
in exchange
for your ski house.

08:15.710 --> 08:17.420
Drum roll, please.

08:17.420 --> 08:21.000
Doris' $20,000
gold-embroidered sofa.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.710
Doris has been trying
to give that thing away

08:22.710 --> 08:24.080
to everyone in town.

08:24.080 --> 08:25.750
It's awful.

08:25.750 --> 08:28.710
It has "Doris" written across it
in huge gold letters, so...

08:28.710 --> 08:30.330
no, thank you.

08:30.330 --> 08:32.120
Would you prefer
to hunt Greg in the woods?

08:33.710 --> 08:35.120
Hi. Mom?

08:35.120 --> 08:37.040
Funny to bump
into you here.

08:37.040 --> 08:38.710
I know you followed me.
I don't need your help.

08:38.710 --> 08:40.330
Oh, but you do.

08:40.330 --> 08:42.380
Hey, Cooper Bradford,
close friend of the family,

08:42.380 --> 08:44.040
come on over here.

08:44.040 --> 08:45.210
Hi, Mrs. Granville.

08:45.210 --> 08:47.000
Cooper?

08:47.000 --> 08:49.670
[ Squeals ]
What a wonderful surprise!

08:49.670 --> 08:51.250
How are your parents?

08:51.250 --> 08:52.580
They're good, yeah.

08:52.580 --> 08:55.210
They are vay-vacationing
in Positano.

08:55.210 --> 08:58.080
Ooh.
What's vay-vacationing?

08:58.080 --> 09:00.620
Well, they were vacationing
in Saint-Jean-Cap-Ferrat

09:00.620 --> 09:02.710
and they needed a vacation
from their vacation.

09:02.710 --> 09:04.670
Oh! [ Laughing ]

09:04.670 --> 09:07.210
Whew. Would you consider
marrying a much older woman?

09:07.210 --> 09:08.830
[ Laughing ] No...

09:08.830 --> 09:10.290
Would you?

09:10.290 --> 09:13.380
Mom, speaking
of Mr. and Mrs. Bradford...

09:13.380 --> 09:14.960
Cooper just informed me
that his parents

09:14.960 --> 09:17.120
are happy to host a table
at this year's Spring Gala.

09:17.120 --> 09:19.620
Mrs. Granville, perhaps
you'd be willing to donate

09:19.620 --> 09:20.880
your Sun Valley house

09:20.880 --> 09:22.500
in exchange for sitting
right next to them?

09:22.500 --> 09:24.790
Oh.

09:24.790 --> 09:26.040
The house is yours.

09:28.380 --> 09:30.080
Would you excuse me
for one moment?

09:31.750 --> 09:33.250
[ Hushed voice ]
What just happened?

09:33.250 --> 09:34.710
Did I just get
the Sun Valley house?

09:34.710 --> 09:36.040
Mom, get woke.

09:36.040 --> 09:37.920
Everyone wants access
to the Bradfords.

09:37.920 --> 09:39.710
They're the most powerful couple
in town.

09:39.710 --> 09:41.580
Sitting at a table with them
for even an hour

09:41.580 --> 09:43.250
can elevate
people's social status.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.960
If we offer up seats
at the Bradfords' table

09:45.960 --> 09:48.170
for big-ticket items,
we're gonna make a killing.

09:48.170 --> 09:52.210
Thus elevating
our social status.

09:52.210 --> 09:53.790
What do you say?
Nancy: Say it again.

09:53.790 --> 09:55.750
Saint-Jean-Cap-Ferrat.

09:55.750 --> 09:57.750
[ Squeals ]
So sophisticated!

09:57.750 --> 10:00.620
[ Laughs ] You tell your parents
I said that, now.

10:00.620 --> 10:03.380
Okay, Oliver,
let's do this.

10:03.380 --> 10:05.960
Finally.
Welcome to my side.

10:05.960 --> 10:07.580
Why do I feel like I'm making
a deal with the Devil?

10:07.580 --> 10:10.830
[ Crashing ]

10:10.830 --> 10:13.120
Oh, thank God.

10:13.120 --> 10:14.250
[ Sighs ]

10:14.250 --> 10:17.460
♪♪

10:17.460 --> 10:22.500
I'm sorry, young man.
The leg has to go.

10:22.500 --> 10:24.830
Glad someone's
having fun.

10:24.830 --> 10:26.380
You just have
to get into it.

10:26.380 --> 10:27.620
Create a character.

10:27.620 --> 10:30.420
For example, I'm a poor
Massachusetts housewife

10:30.420 --> 10:32.040
who, after witnessing
the horrors of war,

10:32.040 --> 10:33.960
has developed
a morphine habit

10:33.960 --> 10:35.000
to deaden the pain.

10:36.670 --> 10:38.080
Hey, girls!

10:38.080 --> 10:39.750
Dad!
Are you wounded?

10:39.750 --> 10:40.960
We'll probably have
to take the leg.

10:40.960 --> 10:42.380
Sorry, pumpkin.

10:42.380 --> 10:44.750
I just wanted to see
how you guys were holding up.

10:44.750 --> 10:46.460
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Taylor, what are you doing?

10:46.460 --> 10:48.170
I'm using a Snapchat filter
where it looks like

10:48.170 --> 10:49.420
you're vomiting rainbows.

10:49.420 --> 10:50.790
Put it away.

10:50.790 --> 10:52.250
I got you out of school
so you could learn

10:52.250 --> 10:54.040
about our great nation,
not play on your phone.

10:54.040 --> 10:55.540
Dad, this sucks.

10:55.540 --> 10:56.960
We're stuck here
in this tent

10:56.960 --> 10:58.210
doing all the crap jobs

10:58.210 --> 11:00.040
while all the guys
are out there having fun.

11:00.040 --> 11:01.750
Don't you think
it's a little uncool that --

11:01.750 --> 11:03.880
My daughter's not giving this a fair shot?
No. That --

11:03.880 --> 11:05.830
You're rejecting one of the most
glorious learning experiences

11:05.830 --> 11:08.580
a person can have? That only the
girls are treated this way.

11:08.580 --> 11:10.000
Especially this day
and age.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.210
But it isn't
this day and age.

11:11.210 --> 11:13.250
That's the whole point.

11:13.250 --> 11:15.540
Corporal Otto,
why aren't you at your post?

11:15.540 --> 11:17.040
Oh, sorry, sir.
I was just checking on my girls.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.540
[ Gasps ]
A phone?

11:18.540 --> 11:20.000
What -- What are you doing
with a pho--

11:20.000 --> 11:22.420
Or rather, what are doing
with some futuristic device

11:22.420 --> 11:24.830
that I don't know about?
Because I'm in the 1700s.

11:24.830 --> 11:26.000
It's no big deal.
I'll just put it away.

11:26.000 --> 11:27.960
Oh. No big deal.

11:27.960 --> 11:30.250
[ Chuckles ]
Okay.

11:30.250 --> 11:34.170
Then maybe it's "no big deal"
that I demote you, Private Otto.

11:34.170 --> 11:36.620
See you
on the battlefield.

11:36.620 --> 11:37.500
Go!

11:39.710 --> 11:40.790
Back to private.

11:40.790 --> 11:42.620
You just flushed
three whole years

11:42.620 --> 11:45.250
of online reenactment class
down the toilet!

11:45.250 --> 11:48.580
♪♪

11:48.580 --> 11:50.670
I've got you down for two seats
at the Bradford table.

11:50.670 --> 11:51.920
And in return,

11:51.920 --> 11:53.960
you'll donate your private jet
for the weekend --

11:53.960 --> 11:56.330
Is that correct?

11:56.330 --> 11:57.330
Great!

11:57.330 --> 11:59.000
Thank you
for your donations.

11:59.000 --> 12:00.710
Put the Bumgarners
on the board!

12:00.710 --> 12:02.380
[ Chuckles ]

12:02.380 --> 12:04.040
Mom,
I got to be honest.

12:04.040 --> 12:05.420
I'm actually having fun.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.420
We're like a mother/son
"Wolf of Wall Street."

12:07.420 --> 12:09.500
I'm Leo.
You're Jonah Hill.

12:09.500 --> 12:12.880
Can't say that I love the
Jonah Hill comparison, but...

12:12.880 --> 12:14.380
this is pretty awesome.

12:14.380 --> 12:16.500
[ Door opens ]

12:16.500 --> 12:18.290
Hey, guys!
How'd it go?

12:18.290 --> 12:21.460
So fun!
I amputated a ton of legs.

12:21.460 --> 12:23.380
Sometimes I accidentally
took the wrong one

12:23.380 --> 12:25.250
just so I could do two.
Mm.

12:25.250 --> 12:27.330
Mom, Dad won't let me go
back to school.

12:27.330 --> 12:29.710
It's a two-day battle,
so no school for you.

12:31.920 --> 12:33.170
What happened
out there?

12:33.170 --> 12:34.880
[ Groans ]
What's happening in here?

12:34.880 --> 12:37.080
Oliver is teaching me
the ways of Westport.

12:37.080 --> 12:39.120
I'm using
Cooper Bradford's parents

12:39.120 --> 12:40.750
as bait to dupe
the rich idiots

12:40.750 --> 12:42.750
into coughing up
fancy auction items.

12:42.750 --> 12:44.830
And we're killin' it.
Mother/son robot dance!

12:44.830 --> 12:47.330
[ Upbeat EDM plays ]

12:47.330 --> 12:48.960
Katie, a moment?

12:48.960 --> 12:51.210
[ Music stops ]

12:51.210 --> 12:53.250
What happened to not getting
sucked into Westport culture?

12:53.250 --> 12:55.000
I know it's weird,
but Oliver is helping me

12:55.000 --> 12:56.330
lock in donations
for the Gala

12:56.330 --> 12:58.250
and has taught me
the wonderful feeling

12:58.250 --> 13:01.040
that comes
with money and power.

13:01.040 --> 13:02.670
I don't like any of this.

13:02.670 --> 13:04.710
I don't like what you just said,
I don't like this board,

13:04.710 --> 13:06.710
and I feel like your hair
may be a little bit different.

13:06.710 --> 13:09.290
Don't listen to him. You're finally
getting respect in this town.

13:09.290 --> 13:10.960
But at what cost?
Don't lose who you are

13:10.960 --> 13:13.080
in pursuit of material gains.
But think of the power.

13:13.080 --> 13:14.790
Surely there must be a
better way to get what you want.

13:14.790 --> 13:16.290
People will want
to know you.

13:16.290 --> 13:17.750
You don't want
to know anyone, Katie.

13:17.750 --> 13:19.120
People will want
to be you.

13:19.120 --> 13:20.380
That's not
what you're about.

13:20.380 --> 13:22.920
And you can finally destroy
Tara Summers.

13:22.920 --> 13:24.330
Winner!
Sorry, Greg.

13:24.330 --> 13:25.670
I'm going
with the kid on this one.

13:25.670 --> 13:26.710
Fine. But for the record,

13:26.710 --> 13:28.000
I don't like the crowd
you're running with.

13:28.000 --> 13:30.380
Who? Oliver?

13:30.380 --> 13:31.670
Yes.

13:31.670 --> 13:34.080
♪♪

13:34.080 --> 13:35.790
[ Sighs ]

13:35.790 --> 13:41.330
♪♪

13:41.330 --> 13:43.290
Katie! Hi!

13:43.290 --> 13:44.710
Don't you look adorable
today.

13:44.710 --> 13:48.120
Someone's clearly heard how
I'm killing it with the Gala.

13:48.120 --> 13:50.080
I have.
And I also heard

13:50.080 --> 13:52.290
that there's one more seat
available at the Bradford table.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.960
Well, by happy coincidence,

13:53.960 --> 13:56.210
our timeshare in the Bahamas
is suddenly available.

13:56.210 --> 13:57.420
Which I'd be happy
to donate.

13:57.420 --> 13:59.790
Oh, really?
That is a happy coincidence.

13:59.790 --> 14:01.170
Your timeshare's
no good here.

14:01.170 --> 14:03.080
And the Bahamas?
Really?

14:03.080 --> 14:04.170
What, are we
filming "Cocktail"?

14:04.170 --> 14:05.210
Move along.

14:09.420 --> 14:10.670
Mom...

14:10.670 --> 14:12.330
Oliver, why didn't you tell me
it was so much fun

14:12.330 --> 14:13.620
being a Westport douchebag?

14:13.620 --> 14:15.380
That's literally
all I talk about.

14:15.380 --> 14:17.250
Mom, bad news.

14:17.250 --> 14:18.920
Cooper Bradford
just got suspended

14:18.920 --> 14:20.960
and might get expelled.
If the school throws him out,

14:20.960 --> 14:23.080
there's no way his parents will
sponsor a table at the Gala.

14:23.080 --> 14:24.500
Oh, man!

14:24.500 --> 14:25.830
Nothing ever goes my way!

14:25.830 --> 14:28.750
First you three kids,
now this!

14:28.750 --> 14:30.080
[ Sighs ]

14:34.380 --> 14:35.420
Principal Ablin?

14:35.420 --> 14:37.460
Oh, hi, Katie.

14:37.460 --> 14:38.920
If you're here
to complain again,

14:38.920 --> 14:42.000
we now have a meat option
on vegan day.

14:42.000 --> 14:45.120
I need your help with
the Cooper Bradford situation.

14:45.120 --> 14:47.250
[ Clears throat ]
You need to unsuspend him.

14:47.250 --> 14:48.960
First,
you're not his parent.

14:48.960 --> 14:50.920
And do you even know what the
Cooper Bradford situation is?

14:50.920 --> 14:52.960
No.
But how bad can it be?

14:52.960 --> 14:54.460
He paid the smart kids
in his math class

14:54.460 --> 14:55.960
to tank their midterm
and lower the curve

14:55.960 --> 14:57.120
so he didn't have to study.

14:57.120 --> 14:58.330
That's terrible.

14:58.330 --> 14:59.580
Yeah. It is.

14:59.580 --> 15:01.460
Back in my day,
if you wanted to cheat,

15:01.460 --> 15:03.330
you'd just write the formulas
on your upper thigh

15:03.330 --> 15:05.210
and then call the teacher
a pervert if he busted you.

15:05.210 --> 15:07.500
It's not so much
how he cheated.

15:07.500 --> 15:08.960
It's that he cheated.

15:08.960 --> 15:10.580
Yeah, I got it,
but here's my problem --

15:10.580 --> 15:12.670
I have to get Cooper
out of trouble,

15:12.670 --> 15:15.620
otherwise the whole Spring Gala
falls apart on me.

15:15.620 --> 15:17.960
And since the Gala
is where a large amount

15:17.960 --> 15:19.460
of the funding for the school
comes from,

15:19.460 --> 15:22.790
without it, other things
fall apart, too.

15:22.790 --> 15:27.580
Like the new planned renovation
of the teachers' lounge

15:27.580 --> 15:29.080
that I just thought of.

15:29.080 --> 15:30.830
Mrs. Otto,
two of our brightest kids

15:30.830 --> 15:32.960
were dis-invited from the
Math-a-lathon because of this.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.330
We're lucky they're
still allowed to compete

15:34.330 --> 15:35.540
in the Biolog-a-lympics.

15:35.540 --> 15:37.210
Okay,
let's me and you talk,

15:37.210 --> 15:38.750
poor person
to poor person.

15:38.750 --> 15:40.330
I do very well,
thank you.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.500
I drive an Elantra.
Stop it.

15:42.500 --> 15:43.750
We're both a couple of poors,
and we know it.

15:43.750 --> 15:45.790
And the rich people
are always using us poors

15:45.790 --> 15:47.210
for what they want.

15:47.210 --> 15:49.290
Don't you think it's time
that a couple of poors

15:49.290 --> 15:51.670
use one of the richies
for what we want?

15:51.670 --> 15:57.420
♪♪

15:57.420 --> 16:00.460
[ Sighs ]

16:00.460 --> 16:04.540
I hear rumor of a very nice sofa
being offered around town.

16:04.540 --> 16:07.420
It says "Doris" on it
in gold?

16:07.420 --> 16:09.380
My cat's name is Doris.

16:09.380 --> 16:12.960
♪♪

16:12.960 --> 16:14.960
Your attention!

16:14.960 --> 16:17.080
The British
have surrounded us!

16:17.080 --> 16:18.580
But before we begin
the massacre,

16:18.580 --> 16:20.210
I'd like to go over
the rules.

16:20.210 --> 16:22.960
As per usual, we will be
using verbal "bangs"

16:22.960 --> 16:24.330
to represent shots fired.

16:24.330 --> 16:26.500
Also, Paul will place stickers
on victims

16:26.500 --> 16:28.330
to indicate
they've been hit.

16:28.330 --> 16:30.250
Okay!
Commence massacre!

16:31.080 --> 16:32.960
Aim! Fire!

16:32.960 --> 16:33.880
Bang!
Bang!

16:33.880 --> 16:36.670
[ Soldiers groaning ]
Fire!

16:36.670 --> 16:37.580
Bang!
Bang!

16:37.580 --> 16:38.500
[ Soldiers groaning ]

16:38.500 --> 16:40.380
-Fire!
-Bang!

16:40.380 --> 16:42.120
[ Solders shouting ]

16:42.120 --> 16:43.620
Fire!

16:43.620 --> 16:45.080
Bang!
Bang!

16:45.080 --> 16:46.620
Fire!

16:46.620 --> 16:49.040
Bang!
Bang!

16:49.040 --> 16:50.750
Bang!
Bang!

16:50.750 --> 16:52.830
♪♪

16:52.830 --> 16:54.420
[ Groans ]

16:54.420 --> 16:56.080
I'm hit!

16:56.080 --> 16:58.000
Shoulder? Really?

16:58.000 --> 16:59.250
Ricochet.

17:02.250 --> 17:03.580
Excellent death, honey.

17:03.580 --> 17:06.120
Thanks, Dad.

17:06.120 --> 17:08.790
[ Grunting dramatically ]

17:08.790 --> 17:13.540
♪♪

17:13.540 --> 17:15.170
[ Continues grunting ]

17:15.170 --> 17:16.380
♪♪

17:16.380 --> 17:17.830
I can't get
these pants dirty.

17:17.830 --> 17:19.540
Last time, they were
so expensive to dry clean.

17:19.540 --> 17:21.540
[ Groaning ]

17:21.540 --> 17:22.670
♪♪

17:22.670 --> 17:24.210
Taylor, die.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.330
No.

17:28.000 --> 17:29.210
You're shot again!
Go down!

17:29.210 --> 17:30.710
No!

17:30.710 --> 17:32.250
[ Imitates cannon firing ]

17:32.250 --> 17:33.620
Boom!

17:33.620 --> 17:36.620
[ Gasps ] Cannonball!

17:36.620 --> 17:37.880
You will die right now,
young lady!

17:37.880 --> 17:39.210
No, Dad!

17:39.210 --> 17:41.250
This is totally unfair!

17:41.250 --> 17:44.040
I can't be a soldier because
it's historically inaccurate?

17:44.040 --> 17:45.580
But people
are just yelling "bang."

17:45.580 --> 17:47.670
And there's a guy
putting stickers on people

17:47.670 --> 17:49.330
to show
they've been shot.

17:49.330 --> 17:50.710
You're fine
overlooking these things

17:50.710 --> 17:52.080
but not letting girls
be soldiers?

17:52.080 --> 17:53.830
Nurse, you will die now!

17:53.830 --> 17:55.170
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

17:55.170 --> 17:56.420
Don't yell
at my daughter.

17:56.420 --> 17:58.290
Back on the ground,
Private Otto,

17:58.290 --> 17:59.710
or I'll send you
to the stockade.

17:59.710 --> 18:01.120
No, you won't, Elliot.

18:01.120 --> 18:02.540
How dare you?

18:02.540 --> 18:05.040
I am Captain Beauregard
of the Fifth Battalion!

18:05.040 --> 18:06.710
No,
you're Elliot Grady.

18:06.710 --> 18:08.290
You sell lambs' wool
car-seat covers

18:08.290 --> 18:10.380
out of a kiosk
in the Stamford Mall.

18:10.380 --> 18:12.580
Stop using words
that haven't been invented yet!

18:12.580 --> 18:14.080
Look,
my daughter is right.

18:14.080 --> 18:16.250
None of this
is 100% accurate.

18:16.250 --> 18:18.040
Jim wears color contacts.

18:18.040 --> 18:20.920
They're stunning, sure,
but come on, accurate?

18:20.920 --> 18:23.540
And I happen to know
that you wear support socks!

18:23.540 --> 18:26.120
[ All gasping ]

18:26.120 --> 18:27.880
I have phlebitis
in my ankles!

18:27.880 --> 18:29.380
All I'm saying is --

18:29.380 --> 18:31.330
is what my daughter's asking for
so wrong?

18:31.330 --> 18:35.210
May I remind you all that
this is the Westport Massacre!

18:35.210 --> 18:36.330
I'm sorry.

18:36.330 --> 18:39.380
This is the
Chunky Soup Westport Massacre!

18:39.380 --> 18:40.420
Paul: I want to bring
my inhaler.

18:40.420 --> 18:42.210
I want to wear
my back brace.

18:42.210 --> 18:45.330
I'd like to bring a football
to throw during down times.

18:45.330 --> 18:47.790
[ Scoffs ] Paul,
get these men in line.

18:49.250 --> 18:50.670
Bang.

18:50.670 --> 18:51.670
Oh, I die?

18:51.670 --> 18:52.790
I die?

18:52.790 --> 18:54.210
Okay,
you know what dies with me?

18:54.210 --> 18:55.790
My Netflix password.

18:55.790 --> 18:57.420
Yeah, didn't think
that one through, did you?

18:57.420 --> 18:59.330
Nope.
No, un-die me!

18:59.330 --> 19:01.210
Thanks, Dad. It was the
right thing to do.

19:01.210 --> 19:02.620
I'm sorry
I didn't support you sooner.

19:02.620 --> 19:04.120
If it makes you feel
any better,

19:04.120 --> 19:05.880
I think I actually get
what you like about history.

19:05.880 --> 19:07.670
You do?
Yeah.

19:07.670 --> 19:09.330
Being a part
of a mini revolution

19:09.330 --> 19:10.880
and standing up
to a tyrant,

19:10.880 --> 19:12.170
it kind of helps me
understand

19:12.170 --> 19:13.710
how those people
really must've felt.

19:13.710 --> 19:14.960
Aw, honey.

19:14.960 --> 19:16.330
I'm so proud of you
for having the courage

19:16.330 --> 19:17.790
to stand up
for what you believe in.

19:17.790 --> 19:20.040
And that you learned about
the Revolution by yourself.

19:20.040 --> 19:22.170
No, Dad. You learned it
to me.

19:22.170 --> 19:23.210
Actually, the proper --

19:23.210 --> 19:24.420
You know what?
Who cares?

19:24.420 --> 19:25.580
We learned it
to each other.

19:25.580 --> 19:26.540
[ Chuckles ]

19:26.540 --> 19:33.120
♪♪

19:33.120 --> 19:35.290
Oh, what's the celebration?
I'm a free man.

19:35.290 --> 19:37.790
Mrs. Otto got Principal Ablin
to unsuspend me.

19:37.790 --> 19:40.380
By giving him Doris' sofa,
thereby saving the Gala.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.000
Wait,
you bribed the principal?

19:42.000 --> 19:43.580
Uh...

19:43.580 --> 19:45.170
Yes, but who cares?

19:45.170 --> 19:46.330
Your Gala's
gonna be a success.

19:46.330 --> 19:48.040
Don't give in.
You fight against this town.

19:48.040 --> 19:49.540
Don't be seduced by it.

19:49.540 --> 19:51.380
No, let it pour you a Scotch
and rub your feet.

19:51.380 --> 19:52.880
Come on, Katie,
I know you're in there.

19:52.880 --> 19:54.420
I'm feeling
a little peckish.

19:54.420 --> 19:55.960
Do you guys have, like,
a charcuterie plate

19:55.960 --> 19:57.750
or some Marcona almonds?

19:57.750 --> 19:59.540
Oh, my God.

19:59.540 --> 20:00.750
Your dad's right.

20:00.750 --> 20:02.170
Wait. No, he's not.

20:02.170 --> 20:03.250
Robot.

20:03.250 --> 20:05.710
[ Upbeat EDM plays ]

20:05.710 --> 20:07.330
[ Music fades ]

20:07.330 --> 20:08.540
Sorry, Oliver.

20:08.540 --> 20:09.960
I did a bad thing.

20:12.000 --> 20:13.250
And you.

20:13.250 --> 20:15.960
What you did at school
was awful,

20:15.960 --> 20:17.460
and you need
to be punished.

20:17.460 --> 20:19.710
You're grounded.

20:19.710 --> 20:23.170
Uh, "grounded" is when
you're forced to stay at home

20:23.170 --> 20:25.250
and lose
all of your privileges.

20:25.250 --> 20:26.670
Mm-hmm.
Stay home?

20:26.670 --> 20:28.380
Great. Guess I get to work
on my bowling

20:28.380 --> 20:29.580
and play with my zebra.

20:29.580 --> 20:32.120
No, you are staying
at our house.

20:32.120 --> 20:33.080
So I get to stay here?

20:34.830 --> 20:35.920
Bueno.

20:35.920 --> 20:37.250
Before I die,

20:37.250 --> 20:39.000
I'm gonna make you sad.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.290
♪♪

20:44.580 --> 20:48.540
♪♪

20:48.540 --> 20:51.710
So, Mrs. Bradford, everything
with the school is fine.

20:51.710 --> 20:55.290
I managed to make sure that
Cooper did not get kicked out.

20:55.290 --> 20:58.670
But I did ground him.

20:58.670 --> 21:00.830
"Grounding"
is when somebody takes away

21:00.830 --> 21:03.170
somebody's privileges.

21:03.170 --> 21:05.420
Okay...well...

21:05.420 --> 21:07.170
then we'll see you
at the Gala, then.

21:07.170 --> 21:08.670
Bye.

21:08.670 --> 21:11.210
I actually feel sorry
for the kid.

21:11.210 --> 21:13.120
I had no idea
you could wash your own car.

21:13.120 --> 21:14.330
This is a first for me.

21:14.330 --> 21:15.710
Oliver:
Yeah, washing our cars

21:15.710 --> 21:17.500
is a first
for the Otto family, too.

21:17.500 --> 21:19.670
I guess this is why Bentley
comes in wet sometimes.

21:19.670 --> 21:21.330
Feeling passed.

21:21.330 --> 21:22.670
Yeah.
